<3184><16780400>:Crafting Project
<3185><16780401>:Craft
<3186><16780402>:This feat represents a PC working on some crafting project and should be targetted at the crafted item. It is usable once per rest as long as the PC is in an area which always allows resting (such as a house, inn room, etc). It cannot be used out in the wild or in a dungeon.

Magic items which require spell to be used in their creation must have those spells cast on them before the item can be worked on.

Potions always take only use (day) to brew. All other magic items are progressed at a rate of 1,000 gp of base cost per day. The PC must pay 1/25th of this cost in XP (to a maximum of 40XP per day).

DMs can use this feat and target an item in order to turn that item into a crafting project which can then be completed by PCs. Targeting an existing craft project turns the project back into a regular, usable item, destroying any progress made.
<3187><16780403>:Forge Ring
<3188><16780404>:(Please Note this Feat Requires DM assistance to use)

Prerequisite
Caster level 12th. 

Benefit
You can create any ring whose prerequisites you meet. Crafting a ring takes one day for each 1,000 gp in its base price. To craft a ring, you must spend 1/25 of its base price in XP and use up raw materials costing one-half of its base price. 

You can also mend a broken ring if it is one that you could make. Doing so costs half the XP, half the raw materials, and half the time it would take to forge that ring in the first place. 

Some magic rings incur extra costs in material components or XP, as noted in their descriptions. You must pay such a cost to forge such a ring or to mend a broken one. 

