<11001><16788217>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: You can change your PC's description field by using PC Tools Custom Button #4.  Descriptions should include only basic physical appearance and presence, and should not include background information or other meta-data that would be unknown to other PCs.
<11002><16788218>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: Doors which have linked area transitions may now be closed from the right-click contextmenu!  Thank you, NWN2 patch 1.23.
<11003><16788219>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: To rest outdoors, use PC tools to pitch a tent to rest near.  This may only be done outdoors in natural-type areas.  Tents may be taken down using the "remove" object interaction in PC tools.  Rangers and druids may rest outdoors without tents.
<11004><16788220>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: Wizards may scribe tradescrolls to allow other wizards to learn spells they have in their spellbooks.  This is accomplished by casting the spell in question at a spellbook item, and costs 25 gp per spell level (or 12 gp for a 0th level spell).  The resulting tradescroll is not useable to cast the spell from, and cannot be sold, but works for copying into spellbooks. 
<11005><16788221>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: The Campfire from PC tools is a container-type object.  If you need a handy place to dispose of useless items (spare bolts, clothing, 0 gp unsellable items), you may put them into the inventory of the Campfire, then use Object Interaction: Remove (PC Tools) to put the fire out, destroying the objects contained within.
<11006><16788222>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: The subdual feat is granted to every ALFA PC, and allows activation or deactivation of nonlethal combat mode as a free action.  Just drag the feat from the character sheet onto a quickslot on the hotbar to set up for quick and easy toggling of nonlethal damage.
<11007><16788223>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: Text macros may be defined in the PC Tools package, by enabling the Text Macro window.  These allow you to hotkey frequent emotes or lines for use when there isn't as much time for typing, such as while scouting or in combat.  NEW FEATURE: you can now pre-program text emotes to go to the party channel for scouting, in addition to the normal and whisper volumes.
<11008><16788224>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: When you remain logged out for more than one day of game-time, available spells and health will be adjusted accordingly to reflect the passage of time.
<11009><16788225>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: Divine casters may restore their spells once per day using their holy symbol objects, or by using PC Tools Custom button 1 ("Pray for Spells").  Innate casters such as Bards, Sorcerers, Spirit Shamans and Favored Souls restore their spells automatically by resting.  Wizards must use their spellbook items to study for new spells.
<11010><16788226>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: In order to save a dying PC, either apply at least one point of magical healing, or apply first aid using the Heal skill (DC15, repeatable) to bandage the bleeding character.  This may be accomplished by using the quickslottable First Aid widget, or using the right-click contextmenu option labeled "Aid".  There are also masterwork first aid kit items for sale with a limited number of charges, which allow this check to be made with a +2 circumstance bonus.  To receive this benefit, use the MW First Aid kit on the dying PC.
<11011><16788227>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: The corpses of fallen player characters are also portable persistent storage objects.  If you remove the "body" item from the inventory of a PC corpse, the placeable will despawn, and the contents will be saved.  When you drop the "body" item, the corpse will reappear with it's contents intact, even over module resets.  Keep in mind though, that corpses decay over time.
<11012><16788228>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: The "Save Character" option on the main screen of PC Tools, as well as the "Save Location" Custom button, both serve to update your character's persistent location in the database, to ensure that you are able to log back in approximately where you logged out from.  Using this option is especially important if you are going to log out right after returning from a dangerous place within the same area (location saves automatically after ATing).
<11013><16788229>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: Healing potions are targetable items in ALFA, and can be used to save a dying or incapacitated PC.  Be careful when using them in combat, not to activate them while your enemy is actively targetted, or they will be wasted.  In combat, potions will only work on yourself or on a disabled PC (0 or fewer hitpoints).  Outside of combat, they may be used on others (simulates giving someone a potion to drink).
<11014><16788230>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: Spell Scrolls that are above a PC's ability to cast now require Caster Level checks to activate successfully.  If a scroll exceeds a caster's attribute limits (wizard with 14 INT attempting to activate a 5th level Cloudkill spell), it will automatically fail unless the caster posseses ranks in Use Magic Device, in which case an Emulate Attribute check will be rolled first in attempt to circumvent the limitation.  Major failure in a scroll activation check may result in a variety of arcane mishaps.
<11015><16788231>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: The Use Magic Device skill allows a character to attempt to activate spellscrolls intended for any class.  One or two Use Magic Device rolls will be required, depending on the spell and whether the user has high enough attributes to control the spell.  Arcane mishaps are far more likely using this skill than when activating a scroll normally.
<11016><16788232>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: To remove a PC Tools VFX prop from your character (spoon, pan, rake, shovel), left-click on the "VFX Props" heading itself, just above all the options.
<11017><16788233>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: Using the subdual feat or widget (or pressing the PC Tools custom button) activates Subdual mode, for non-lethal combat.  This allows you to subdue other players, or even to incapacitate monsters or hostile NPCs temporarily.  Remember, just because you have subdual mode on, does not mean your opponent does as well.  Subdual works both armed and unarmed, and allows use of modes such as Expertise and Power Attack, but does not work with ranged weapons or magic.  There is also a small risk of doing real damage in a subdual attack. Subdual/nonlethal damage is healed by normal healing spells, and fades with time much more quickly than normal damage.  
<11018><16788234>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: Do not run, unless the situation calls for it urgently.  In many cases the exterior areas of ALFA's servers are meant to represent miles of territory, so it is best to keep time spent running to a minimum.  In order to make your character walk, simply activate tracking mode, search mode, or use shift-left-click to set your destination.  (Search mode will not slow elven PCs to a walking pace, and shift-click on a creature may order an attack, so aim carefully if you use this method.
<11019><16788235>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: Party Chat (/p) should be used for scouting only unless specifically requested by a DM.  This mode of communication excludes nearby PCs who are not in your party, which can cause undue confusion, and passes all text to all DMs logged in, which can make their job difficult.  A Dungeon Master flooded with unwanted text is, generally speaking, not a happy DM.
<11020><16788236>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: Seamless ATs are one of the methods of transitioning between adjacent areas, which allow more freedom in the arrival point.  Upon entering a Seamless AT, you will see a message like "Moving West...".  If you back away from the edge of the area quickly, it will cancel the transition.  You will also be warned if there is danger in the immediate area you are about to move into; and have additional time in which to cancel such a transition.
<11021><16788237>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: Resting may only be done under certain conditions, such as inside an inn room or outdoors near a tent.  Resting will heal damage equal to the character's level and help alleviate attribute damage, as well as prepare them to use magic again.  Praying or Studying for spells may be done anywhere.
<11022><16788238>:ALFA Core Rules Tip:  Adventuring alone is not recommended.  A PC's chances of recovering from an attack that brings him or her into negative hitpoints are exceedingly small without outside assistance.  Most characters that die, die alone.  
<11023><16788239>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: You may italicize normal text by surrounding it in < i > and < /i > tags.
<11024><16788240>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: To check the current time of day onserver, use the "Check Time" button on the main screen of PC Tools.
<11025><16788241>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: To access PC tools for emotes and custom functions, right-click on the ground, and select the "PC Tools" option from the bottom of the list.  You may have to right-click and hold for several seconds, depending on your settings.
<11026><16788242>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: The PC Tools window may be minimized by right-clicking on the box in the upper left-hand corner of the interface.  Left-clicking on the minimized pane restores the screen.  It may also be dragged to the side and out of the way using this icon.
<11027><16788243>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: Disable AI and activate "Puppet Mode" in your settings to keep your PC from making it's own (dubious) combat decisions, like drinking potions and using scrolls you didn't ask it to.  This may need to be done each time you log in, depending.
<11028><16788244>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: To log the text from the game for later review, find your nwn2player.ini file in your /my documents/Neverwinter Nights 2/ folder.  Under [Game Options], add the line "ClientChatLogging=1" and save the change.  This will generate a logfile called "nwclientLog1.txt" containing everything from the chat window.  The logfile is buried in HDD:/Documents and Settings/(username)/Local Settings/Temp/NWN2/LOGS/ where (username) is your Windows username, and Local Settings is a hidden folder.  This file will overwrite each time the game restarts, so remember to rename it before restarting.
<11029><16788245>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: Do not patch Neverwinter Nights 2 until/unless instructed to by Admin.  Whenever a new patch to the game is released, it must be accounted for in the haks and servers before it is formally adopted.  If prompted to patch when connecting to Gamespy, decline and check the forums to see when your server will be patching.  Otherwise, you may be unable to log in until the servers patch, which may be days to weeks later.
<11030><16788246>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: If you see a green sparkle at a door or the edge of an area, it means another PC or NPC is transitioning into your area at that point.  Since it takes some time to load an area in the client, this helps avoid unintentional cross-ATing (missing a PC directly in your path because you were both loading the screen at the same time).  If you do not wish your approach to be noticed by other PCs who may be near the destination of an AT, activate stealth mode before ATing to supress this effect.
<11031><16788247>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: Lutes, Drums, and Flutes are now playable instruments, thanks to BrockFanning's TKL Performer scripts.  Just equip one and start practicing up.  GUI tutorials may be found within the musical instrument interface via the "?" buttons.
<11032><16788248>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: Bastard Swords now require Martial Weapons Proficiency, rather than Exotic. Unless the wielder also has Monkey Grip or Exotic Weapons Proficiency, use of a bastard sword requires two hands.  
<11033><16788249>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: Your character will accumulate XP slowly just for being logged in and roleplaying.  This is tracked by "RP Increments" and "Location Increments".  This XP is awarded after your next login.
<11034><16788250>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: Your character may speak in the various languages he or she knows, by selecting the "VoiceEntry" option on the far right of the DMFI toolbar.  Text entered into the box that opens after you select a language will be translated for others who speak the same language.  Don't be alarmed if the box is labelled "undercommon", you will be speaking the same language you selected.
<11035><16788251>:ALFA Tip: You are 2 characters at a time in ALFA. They must play on different servers.  If you roll up and start playing a third PC, one of your prior character(s) is considered "retired".  You are still allowed to play as many characters as you like on Beta Servers for testing purposes.
<11036><16788252>:ALFA Tip: Sending tells (/t, or player chat window) is a good way to coordinate meetings with other players on the server.  In most cases, you should be able to brainstorm an in-character way for your characters to cross paths if you so choose.  
<11037><16788253>:ALFA Tip: ALFA is a permadeath world.  Once your PC is dead, there is no coming back, unless rare and powerful magic is used.
<11038><16788254>:ALFA Tip: There is no "Save Game" in ALFA.  Make decisions accordingly!
<11039><16788255>:ALFA Tip: Extraordinary PCs (Aasimar, Tieflings, Genasi, and Favored Souls) may be played in ALFA if the character bio is approved.  Contact the Head Dungeon Master (HDM) of your server to find out how.
<11040><16788256>:ALFA Tip: Your character doesn't know how many XP it needs until next level.  Don't rush it!
<11041><16788257>:ALFA Tip: Do not loot your own corpse!
<11042><16788258>:ALFA Tip: Walk, don't run.
<11043><16788259>:ALFA Tip: The light at the end of the tunnel just might be an incoming Fireball spell.
<11044><16788260>:ALFA Tip: Stay on the roads for safety.
<11045><16788261>:ALFA Tip: Torches help you see at night, but they also help you be seen by others.
<11046><16788262>:ALFA Tip: Consider the novelty of a functional childhood for your next PC.  There can only be so many orphaned bastard sons and daughters of fallen noble houses running around.
<11047><16788263>:ALFA Tip: Updates to ALFA's haks and walkmeshes will be downloaded automatically on attempting to connect to a Live server.  If you are planning a trip to a new server for the first time, you can log into the destination server beforehand to get the walkmesh files all downloaded to make the server transition quick and easy.
<11048><16788264>:ALFA Tip: If you are playing a divine caster (cleric, druid, paladin, or ranger), spend some time getting to know the lore and dogma of your character's diety.  Such familiarity may be expected by DMs and other players, and can be great material for roleplay.
<11049><16788265>:ALFA Tip: Druids may not wear metal armor, even if they are multiclassed.  They may, however, use any weapon with which they are proficient.  
<11050><16788266>:ALFA Tip: Paladins and monks have limitations on multiclassing, check the ALFA forums for details.
<11051><16788267>:ALFA Tip: Party up for quests.  Most scripted static quests from NPCs allow a group to accomplish the task together.
<11052><16788268>:ALFA Tip: Once you have come up with a backstory for your character, send it to an active DM as a private message on the forums, so they can post it for the rest of the team.  This helps DMs come up with plots that would be interesting to your character, and get a sense of what he or she is about. Its also possibly worth a little XP!
<11053><16788269>:ALFA Tip: If you have friends who you think might enjoy ALFA, encourage them to apply.  
<11054><16788270>:ALFA Tip: Remember to blink.
<11055><16788271>:ALFA Tip: The quickest route to the grave is going alone.
<11056><16788272>:ALFA Tip: Armor tends not to be very comfortable to wear while eating, drinking, chatting, or sleeping.  Diversify your wardrobe!
<11057><16788273>:ALFA Tip: In polite company, it is considered poor manners to have a weapon equipped.  
<11058><16788274>:ALFA Tip: If you are interested in helping bring ALFA's world to life, consider applying to become a Dungeon Master via the website, www.alandfaraway.info
<11059><16788275>:ALFA Tip: The passage of time is somewhat arbitrary in ALFA.  Try to be ambigious when possible ("some time ago", "recently", "of late", "soon", "in a few days") to avoid confusion.  You can clarify actual times with other players and DMs using private tells.
<11060><16788276>:ALFA Tip: When something is clearly a technical bug, ex: floating trees, water that doesn't line up with the shore, broken walkmesh, or a house part-buried in the terrain, this should be reported via the forums at www.alandfaraway.info - and should not be played as in-character fact.
<11061><16788277>:ALFA Tip: CvC, or Character versus Character combat, is permitted in ALFA when in-character (IC).  However, the DM staff should be informed of premeditated CvC actions, and a DM should ideally be present to adjudicate when possible.
<11062><16788278>:ALFA Core Rules Tip: Dynamic weapon VFX are now available!  Use the custom buttons in PC tools to toggle these on and off, they will bind to the next appropriate item equipped for ease of use.
