<13039><16790255>:<color=Gold><b>Loremaster</b></color>

<color=Red>(PRESTIGE CLASS: This class is not available at character creation and must be unlocked by meeting special requirements, listed below.)</color>

Loremasters are spellcasters who concentrate on knowledge, valuing lore and secrets over gold. They uncover secrets that they then use to better themselves mentally, physically, and spiritually.

Characters without at least one level of wizard, sorcerer, cleric, or druid gain little benefit for becoming a loremaster. Paladins, rangers, and bards might gain some benefit, but overall, it would be minor. Loremasters sometimes gather in secluded cabals but are more often found as members of an order attached to a university, a library, or some other source of information.

They're likely to earn extra money as sages and information brokers, pouring their wages into their own research. A loremaster might also adopt a position as a wise one in a community, or even as its leader, drawing upon her knowledge to help others.

<color=Gold>Requirements:</color>

<b>Skills:</b> Knowledge (Any) 10 Ranks**, Knowledge (Any) 10 ranks

<b>Feats:</b> Able Learner OR 3 metamagic/item creation feats

<b>Spellcasting:</b> able to cast 3rd level Arcane spells OR Divine spells.

<b>Special:</b> PC must know divination spells and have shown a desire to persue knowledge (this is a soft requirement and at DM discretion)

<color=Gold>Class Features:</color>

- <b>Hit Die:</b> d4

- <b>Base Attack Bonus:</b> Low.

- <b>High Saves:</b> Will.

- <b>Weapon Proficiencies:</b> None.

- <b>Armor Proficiencies:</b> None.

- <b>Skill Points:</b> 4 + Int modifier.

- <b>Class Skills:</b> Appraise, Concentration,
Craft (alchemy), Decipher Script, Gather Information, Handle Animals, Heal, Knowledge (all skills taken individually), Perform, Profession, Speak Language, Spellcraft, and Use Magic Device.

<color=Gold>Class Abilities:</color>


- <b>Spellcasting Progression:</b> At Every level the Loremaster gains additional spells per day and spells known as if they had also progressed in their original spellcasting class, if they character had more than one class they must choose one of these classes upon first levelling in Loremaster.

-<b>+2 Reflex:</b>  as the lightning Reflex feat 

-<b>Lore:</b> The Loremaster can recall various facts, this ability works identically to Bardic Knowledge and requires DM intervention.

-<b>+2 Fortitude:</b> As Great Fortitude feat

-<b>Bonus Languages:</b> at 4th and 8th and additional Language needs to be assigned.

-<b>Dodge:</b> As feat

-<b>Greater Lore:</b> Grants spell like ability to cast identify */day

-<b>Bonus Spell Slots: </b> The character gains a bonus level 1 spell slot at 7th level and a bonus level 2 slot at 9th level.

-<b>True Lore:<b> Grants spell like ability to cast legend Lore 1/day 


