<13267><16790483>:Balance
<13268><16790484>:Clerics with the balance domain work by contemplation and reflection, casting spells that promote clarity.

<b>Domain Special Abilities and Bonus Spells:</b> Once per day, as a free action, you may add your Wisdom modifier to your armor class. This bonuc lasts for 1 round per cleric level. Make Whole (1), Calm Emotions (2), Clarity of Mind (3), Dismissal (4), Mass Sanctuary (5), Banishment (6), Word of Balance (7), Protection from Spells (8), Weighed in the Balance (9)
<13269><16790485>:Cavern
<13270><16790486>:Clerics with the cavern domain are at home underground, able to move through often-confusing passages with ease and comfort.

<b>Domain Special Abilities and Bonus Spells:</b> Clerics with cavern domain receive stonecunning, as a dwarf. Detect Secret Doors (1), Darkness (2), Meld Into Stone (3), Leomund's Secure Shelter (4), Passwall (5), Find the Path (6), Maw of Stone (7), Earthquake (8), Imprisonment (9)

<i>Note that some of the spells are RP spells, and may not be useful without a DM</i>
<13271><16790487>:Charm
<13272><16790488>:Clerics with the charm domain are especially-gifted in the arts of persuasion, and have powers to help them convince others to help them.

<b>Domain Special Abilities and Bonus Spells:</b> Clerics with charm domain may increase their charisma by 4 for one minute once per day. Charm Person (1), Calm Emotions (2), Suggestion (3), Good Hope (4), Charm Monster(5), Geas (6), Insanity (7), Demand (8), Dominate Monster (9).

<i>Note that some of the spells are RP spells, and may not be useful without a DM</i>
<13273><16790489>:Drow
<13274><16790490>:Clerics with the drow domain are paragons of drow value, being nimble well equipped to handle matters of subterfuge.

<b>Domain Special Abilities and Bonus Spells:</b> Clerics with charm domain receives Lightning Reflexes for free. Cloak of Dark Power (1), Clairaudience/Clairvoyance (2), Suggestion (3), Discern Lies (4), Spiderform (5), Greater Dispel Magic (6), Word of Chaos (7), Greater Planar Ally (8), Gate (9)

<i>Note that some of the spells are RP spells, and may not be useful without a DM</i>
<13275><16790491>:Dwarf
<13276><16790492>:Clerics with the dwarf domain are paragons of dwarven value, being stalwart and creative, equipped to build and hold their ground.

<b>Domain Special Abilities and Bonus Spells:</b> Clerics with dwarf domain receive Great Fortitude for free. Magic Weapon (1), Bear's Endurance (2), Glyph of Warding (3), Greater Magic Weapon (4), Fabricate (5), Stone Tell (6), Dictum (7), Protection from Spells (8), Elemental Swarm (9)

<i>Note that some of the spells are RP spells, and may not be useful without a DM</i>
<13277><16790493>:Elf
<13278><16790494>:Clerics with the elf domain are paragons of elven value, being graceful and precise, living comfortably in the forests.

<b>Domain Special Abilities and Bonus Spells:</b> Clerics with elf domain receive Point Blank Shot for free. True Strike (1), Cat's Grace (2), Snare (3), Tree Stride (4), Commune with Nature (5), Find the Path (6), Liveoak (7), Sunburst (8), Antipathy (9)

<i>Note that some of the spells are RP spells, and may not be useful without a DM</i>
<13279><16790495>:Fate
<13280><16790496>:Clerics with the fate domain have their fingers on the pulse of destiny, having aware of how things are doomed, or destined, to unfold.

<b>Domain Special Abilities and Bonus Spells:</b> Clerics with fate domain receive Uncanny Dodge for free. True Strike (1), Augury (2), Bestow Curse (3), Divination (4), Mark of Justice (5), Geas/Quest (6), Vision (7), Moment of Prescience (8), Foresight (9)

<i>Note that some of the spells are RP spells, and may not be useful without a DM</i>
<13281><16790497>:Moon
<13282><16790498>:Clerics with the moon domain know well the powers of lunar cycle, and gain power over creatures influenced by it, such as lycanthropes.

<b>Domain Special Abilities and Bonus Spells:</b> Clerics with moon domain may turn lycanthropes as if they were undead. Faerie Fire (1), Moonbeam (2), Moon Blade (3), Good Hope (4), Moon Path (5), Permanent Image (6), Insanity (7), Animal Shapes (8), Moonfire (9)

<i>Note that some of the spells are RP spells, and may not be useful without a DM</i>
<13283><16790499>:Orc
<13284><16790500>:Clerics with the orc domain are paragons of orcish virtue, acting with wrath and vigor in response to obstacles.

<b>Domain Special Abilities and Bonus Spells:</b> Clerics with orc domain may use a special smite attack once per day. This attack does additional damage to those who don't follow the orcish gods. Cause Fear (1), Produce Flame (2), Prayer (3), Divine Power (4), Prying Eyes (5), Eyebite (6), Blasphemy (7), Cloak ofChaos (8), Power Word: Kill (9)

<i>Note that some of the spells are RP spells, and may not be useful without a DM</i>
<13285><16790501>:Planning
<13286><16790502>:Clerics with the planning domains are masters of strategy, gifted with abilities to allow them to prepare for the long term.

