<i>Note that some of the spells are RP spells, and may not be useful without a DM</i>
<13289><16790505>:Repose
<13290><16790506>:Clerics with the repose domain are those who oversee the process of death, but do so as the impartial distributors of end of life, rather than by the wanton slaughter of clerics of the death domain.

<b>Domain Special Abilities and Bonus Spells:</b> Clerics with the repose domain may perform a touch of death once per day, which kills a target with less than 1d6 hit points per cleric level, per the rules for dealing a magical death touch attack. Hide from Undead (1), Gentle Repose (2), Speak with Dead (3), Death Ward (4), Slay Living (5), Undeath to Death (6), Destruction (7), Surelife (8), Wail of the Banshee (9)

<i>Note that some of the spells are RP spells, and may not be useful without a DM</i>
<13291><16790507>:Retribution
<13292><16790508>:Clerics with the retribution domain are concerned with the distribution of punishment for crimes past, and are invested well in defense and countering.

<b>Domain Special Abilities and Bonus Spells</b>: Clerics with the retribution domain may perform a smite attack once per day, doing additional damage to targets who do not share their faith. Shield of Faith (1), Bear's Endurance (2), Speak with Dead (3), Fire Shield (4), Mark of Justice (5), Banishment (6), Spell Turning (7), Discern Location (8), Storm of Vengeance (9)

<i>Note that some of the spells are RP spells, and may not be useful without a DM</i>
<13293><16790509>:Rune
<13294><16790510>:Clerics with the rune domain are concerned heavily with written records and the magical meanings of writing.

